    • Method Detail

      • stateChanged

        public void stateChanged(int state)
        This method tells the user if the Bluetooth Mesh Stack in the library is initialised or/and deinitiliased. The user must be careful to not initialise it before deinitialise the previous session.
        Parameters:
        state - Integer containing the state of the Bluetooth Mesh Stack in the Library
        See Also:
        BluetoothMesh.BluetoothMesh(Context, MeshCallback)

        Parameters:
        name - String with the name of the Network
        index - Integer containing the index of the network key
        netKey - byte array containing the network key

        netKeyIndex - Integer containing the index of the network key
        appKeyIndex - Integer containing the index of the application key
        appKey - byte array containing the application key

      • gattWrite

        public void gattWrite(int gattHandle,
                      byte[] send)
        This method is called when the BluetoothMesh wants to send a message to the node/unprovisioned device.
        Parameters:
        gattHandle - Integer containing the handle of the gatt connection
        send - byte[] containing the message to be writen to the meshUnprovisionedInChar or meshProxyInChar
        See Also:
        BluetoothMesh.meshUnprovisionedInChar, BluetoothMesh.meshProxyInChar

      • didSuccessProvision

        public void didSuccessProvision(int meshAddress,
                                byte[] deviceUuid,
                                int status)
        This method is called when a provisioning session is completed. This is only used when provisionDevice is called.
        Parameters:
        meshAddress - Integer containing the node unicast address
        deviceUuid - byte[] containing device uuid
        status - Integer containing the status of operation

      • didReceiveDCD

        public void didReceiveDCD(byte[] dcd,
                          int status)
        This method is called when the BluetoothMesh receives a DCD request callback
        Parameters:
        dcd - byte[] containing the device's composition data
        status - Integer containing the status of the operation

      • disconnectionRequest

        public void disconnectionRequest(int gattHandle)
        This method is called when the BluetoothMesh request a disconnection from the node. It only happens after provisioning.
        Parameters:
        gattHandle - Integer containing the handle of the gatt connection

      • gattRequest

        public void gattRequest(int gattHandle)
        This method is called when the BluetoothMesh confirms that the GATT connection is open.
        Parameters:
        gattHandle - Integer containing the handle of the gatt connection

      • didExportRequest

        public void didExportRequest(android.content.Intent shareIntent)
        This method is called as a callback from the export keys (export_json_securely) method. This is not related with the Bluetooth Mesh Library itself, but it uses the database from the BluetoothMesh.
        Parameters:
        shareIntent - Intent used to enable the app to send the json to other apps in the Mobile.

      • didOOBAuthdisplay

        public void didOOBAuthdisplay(byte[] uuid,
                              int input_action,
                              int input_size,
                              byte[] auth_data)
        This method is called as a callback from the Bluetooth Mesh Library when it expects the UI to display an OOB authentication key
        Parameters:
        uuid - byte[] containing the device mesh uuid.
        input_action - Integer containing the input action that the node requests
        input_size - Integer containing the size of the auth_data
        auth_data - byte[] containing the auth_data to be display in the UI

      • didOOBAuthRequest

        public void didOOBAuthRequest(byte[] uuid,
                              int output_action,
                              int output_size)
        This method is called as a callback from the Bluetooth Mesh Library when it expects the user to input an OOB authentication key
        Parameters:
        uuid - byte[] containing the device mesh uuid.
        output_action - Integer containing the output action that the node requests
        output_size - Integer containing the size of the auth_data

      • didCompleteConfig

        public void didCompleteConfig(ConfigOperation previous_cfg,
                              ConfigOperation next_cfg)
        This method is called when a configuration complete callback is received in the Bluetooth Mesh Library
        Parameters:
        previous_cfg - ConfigOperation containing the configuration information
        next_cfg - ConfigOperation containing the next configuration information in queue (null if empty)

      • statusCallback

        public void statusCallback(int model,
                           int device_address,
                           int current_status,
                           int target_status,
                           int remaining_ms)
        This method is called when there is a status callback response from a node regarding status change (e.g Toggling a Generic OnOff Server) This feature is limited for Generic OnOff Server, Generic Level Server and Light Lightness Server
        Parameters:
        model - Integer containing the model id for this status
        device_address - Integer containing the node's mesh address
        current_status - Integer containing the current status value
        target_status - Integer containin the targer status value
        remaining_ms - Integer containing the remaining time in milliseconds. This is the timer for the model to construct a response message.
